## 5. Design Requirements

### 5.1 Visual Identity

#### Color Palette
| Color | Hex | Usage |
|-------|-----|-------|
| Background | #0A0A0A | Primary background |
| Surface | #1A1A1A | Cards, chat bubbles (Grump) |
| Border | #333333 | Dividers, outlines |
| Accent | #FF6B6B | Highlights, Grump's mood indicator |
| Text Primary | #E0E0E0 | Main text |
| Text Secondary | #888888 | Timestamps, hints |
| User Bubble | #2A2A2A | User message background |

#### Typography
- **Primary Font:** SF Pro (system) or Inter
- **Grump's Voice:** Slightly different weight/style to distinguish his messages
- **No Emojis in Grump Messages** (except rare ðŸ˜’ or ðŸ’€)

#### Avatar Design
- Minimalist face with angry eyebrows
- Frowning/flat mouth expression
- Subtle glow effect matching accent color
- Micro-animations for different states:
  - Idle: Slow blink, slight movement
  - Typing: Eye roll animation
