## 6. Technical Requirements

### 6.1 Platform & Compatibility
| Requirement | Specification |
|-------------|---------------|
| Platform | iOS (iPhone primary, iPad secondary) |
| Minimum iOS Version | iOS 16.0+ |
| Device Support | iPhone 12 and newer (optimized) |
| Orientation | Portrait only (MVP) |

### 6.2 Architecture

#### Frontend
- **Framework:** SwiftUI (preferred) or UIKit
- **State Management:** Combine / SwiftUI native
- **Local Storage:** CoreData or SwiftData for chat history

#### Backend / AI
| Option | Description | Considerations |
|--------|-------------|----------------|
| Anthropic API (Claude) | Direct integration with Claude API | Best quality, requires API management |
| OpenAI API | GPT-4 with custom system prompt | Alternative, widely supported |
| Custom Fine-tuned Model | Self-hosted model trained on Grump persona | Most control, highest complexity |
| Hybrid | Primary + fallback provider | Reliability |

#### API Layer
- RESTful API or direct SDK integration
- Request queuing for poor connectivity
- Response caching where appropriate
- Rate limiting handling

### 6.3 Performance Requirements
| Metric | Target |
|--------|--------|
| App Launch | < 2 seconds to interactive |
| Message Send â†’ Response Start | < 1.5 seconds (perceived) |
| Typing Indicator | Immediate on send |
| Crash Rate | < 0.1% |
| ANR Rate | < 0.1% |

### 6.4 Security & Privacy
- No account required (MVP) â€” anonymous usage
- Local chat storage (not synced to cloud in MVP)
- API keys secured (not exposed in client)
- Privacy policy compliant (GDPR, CCPA considerations)
- Optional: End-to-end encryption for chat history

### 6.5 Analytics
- Anonymous usage analytics (with consent)
- Track: Session length, messages sent, feature usage, retention
- Crash reporting (Crashlytics / Sentry)
- A/B testing capability for prompts/features

